'''Graeme Manson''' is a Canadian screenwriter and producer. He is best known for his work on [[BBC America]] and [[Space (Canadian TV channel)|Space]] [[Science fiction|sci-fi]] [[Television program|television series]] ''[[Orphan Black]]''.

==Career==
He co-wrote the 1997 film ''[[Cube (film)|Cube]]'' and has written for television for several years since, including ''[[The Bridge (Canadian TV series)|The Bridge]]'', ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]'', and ''[[Being Erica]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/whatever-linda-web-series-tv-series-mark-gordon-company-hannah-cheesman-1201741078/|title=‘Whatever, Linda’ Web Series To Get TV Adaptation By ‘Orphan Black’ Co-Creator & Mark Gordon Co.|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=2016-04-20|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-09-17|language=en-US}}</ref>

With [[John Fawcett (director)|John Fawcett]], he is the co-creator and executive producer of the acclaimed and award-winning television series ''[[Orphan Black]]'', for which he also has written many episodes. The two previously had collaborated on the 2001 film ''[[Lucky Girl (2001 film)|Lucky Girl]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://arts.nationalpost.com/2014/04/19/orphan-blacks-foster-parents-how-john-fawcett-and-graeme-manson-came-to-create-a-canadian-hit/ |title=Orphan Black’s foster parents: How John Fawcett and Graeme Manson came to create a Canadian hit |work=[[National Post]] |first=David |last=Berry |date=April 19, 2014 |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref>

He will be the executive producer for the upcoming TV adaptation of ''[[Whatever, Linda]]'', an award-winning [[web series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/whatever-linda-web-series-tv-series-mark-gordon-company-hannah-cheesman-1201741078/|title=‘Whatever, Linda’ Web Series To Be Adapted For TV By Mark Gordon Co - Deadline|author=Nellie Andreeva|work=Deadline}}</ref>

==Awards==
With John Fawcett, he received the 2015 CFC Award for Creative Excellence from the [[Canadian Film Centre]] for his work on ''Orphan Black''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cfccreates.com/news/490-graeme-manson-and-john-fawcett-presented-with-2015-cfc-award-for-creative-excellence|title=Graeme Manson and John Fawcett Presented with 2015 CFC Award for Creative Excellence|publisher=}}</ref> He has also won 3 [[Canadian Screen Awards]], a [[Hugo Award]], and a [[Writers Guild of Canada]] award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0543919/awards|title=Graeme Manson|website=IMDb|access-date=2016-07-23}}</ref>

